=== Stone Figure === [[File:石人山古墳石人.JPG|thumb|upright|Stone figure]] In front of the stone chamber, a {{ill|stone human figure|ja|石人|12=draft|12=draft}}, Historic Site1 as an Important designation1 of Japan, is displayed in the {{ill|Sekijin Shrine|ja|石人社|12=draft|12=draft}}. This armed figure, which gave the kofun its name, stands with its back to the chamber. The figure, along with a similar one from {{ill|Ishigamiyama Kofun|ja|石神山古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Miyama, Fukuoka|ja|みやま市|12=draft|12=draft}}, is among the oldest of its kind in the Southern Chikugo region.<ref name=iwato />
Carved from Aso welded tuff, the figure measures approximately 1.8 meters in height. It wears a triangular plate cuirass and {{ill|kusazuri|ja|草摺|12=draft|12=draft}}, and a groove on its left side indicates where a stone sword was once attached.<ref name=iwato />
The figure's face is now eroded, and its upper body patterns are unclear. Historical sketches from the Edo period depict its original appearance, showing eyes, a nose, and a mouth. It is believed that the figure became worn over time due to a folk practice of touching or striking it to cure physical ailments.<ref>[http://www.city.chikugo.lg.jp/kankou/_1070/_6135/_1088.html 石人山古墳の武装石人 - 筑後市]</ref>
== Access == * {{ill|JR Kyushu|ja|JR九州|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|Kagoshima Main Line|ja|鹿児島本線|12=draft|12=draft}}, 8 minutes by taxi from {{ill|Nishimuta Station|ja|西牟田駅|12=draft|12=draft}}. * From {{ill|Hainuzuka Station|ja|羽犬塚駅|12=draft|12=draft}}, take a {{ill|Nishitetsu Bus|ja|西鉄バス|12=draft|12=draft}} towards {{ill|Nishitetsu Kurume Station|ja|西鉄久留米駅|12=draft|12=draft}}, disembark at "Ichijō," and walk 15 minutes (1.2 km). * 4.8 km from {{ill|Hirokawa Interchange|ja|広川インターチェンジ|12=draft|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Kyushu Expressway|ja|九州自動車道|12=draft|12=draft}}.
